## ⚙️ Local Development Setup

To test and run the ParodyMart codebase on your local system, execute the following instructions:

### 1. Clone Project Directory Repository

```bash
git clone [https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/parody-mart.git](https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/parody-mart.git)
cd parody-mart

```

### 2. Construct and Initialize Python Virtual Environment

```bash
python -m venv venv

# On Windows systems (Command Prompt):
venv\Scripts\activate
# On macOS / Linux systems:
source venv/bin/activate

```

### 3. Install Frozen Application Packages Checklist

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt

```

### 4. Create Hidden Environment Variables Container

Construct a file named `.env` exactly inside your root workspace directory and input your runtime keys:

```env
SECRET_KEY=b9a826c71120f3e843ab721c9aef11
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://your_neon_username:your_password@your_neon_host/neondb?sslmode=require

```

### 5. Execute Relational Seeder Script

Run the automation seeder to compile table blueprints straight to your Neon cloud cluster and plant your mock products:

```bash
python seed.py

```

### 6. Boot Development Server Instance

```bash
python run.py

```

Open your web browser tool and access: `http://127.0.0.1:5000/`

---

## ⚠️ Free Cloud Tier Hosting Disclaimer

> **IMPORTANT CONFIGURATION NOTE:** ParodyMart uses Render's free deployment web container tiers. Free infrastructure containers automatically enter a sleep cycle after 15 minutes of inactivity. When launching the live URL for the first time, allow **up to 60 seconds** for Render's routing mechanics to boot the container context back online. Thank you!

